description: Creates a vehicle, which is an instance of a vehicle model (model manifest). Vehicles created from the same vehicle model consist of the same signals inherited from the vehicle model. For more information, see Create a vehicle (AWS CLI) in the Amazon Web Services IoT FleetWise Developer Guide.

parameters.name: vehicleName
parameters.description: The unique ID of the vehicle to create.

parameters.name: modelManifestArn
parameters.description: The Amazon Resource Name ARN of a vehicle model.

parameters.name: decoderManifestArn
parameters.description: The ARN of a decoder manifest.

parameters.name: attributes
parameters.description: Static information about a vehicle in a key-value pair. For example: "engineType" : "1.3 L R2" To use attributes with Campaigns or State Templates, you must include them using the request parameters dataExtraDimensions and/or metadataExtraDimensions (for state templates only) when creating your campaign/state template. (string) --- (string) ---

parameters.name: associationBehavior
parameters.description: An option to create a new Amazon Web Services IoT thing when creating a vehicle, or to validate an existing Amazon Web Services IoT thing as a vehicle. Default:

parameters.name: tags
parameters.description: Metadata that can be used to manage the vehicle. (dict) --- A set of key/value pairs that are used to manage the resource. The tag's key. The tag's value.

parameters.name: stateTemplates
parameters.description: Associate state templates with the vehicle. You can monitor the last known state of the vehicle in near real time. (dict) --- The state template associated with a vehicle. State templates contain state properties, which are signals that belong to a signal catalog that is synchronized between the Amazon Web Services IoT FleetWise Edge and the Amazon Web Services Cloud. The unique ID of the state template. The update strategy for the state template. Vehicles associated with the state template can stream telemetry data with either an onChange or periodic update strategy. periodic (dict) --- Vehicles associated with the state template will stream telemetry data during a specified time period. The length of time between state template updates. A unit of time. A number of time units. onChange (dict) --- Vehicles associated with the state template will stream telemetry data when there is a change.

nested_params.name: identifier
nested_params.description: The unique ID of the state template.

nested_params.name: stateTemplateUpdateStrategy
nested_params.description: The update strategy for the state template. Vehicles associated with the state template can stream telemetry data with either an onChange or periodic update strategy.

nested_params.name: periodic
nested_params.description: Vehicles associated with the state template will stream telemetry data during a specified time period.

nested_params.name: stateTemplateUpdateRate
nested_params.description: The length of time between state template updates.

nested_params.name: onChange
nested_params.description: Vehicles associated with the state template will stream telemetry data when there is a change.

nested_items.name: vehicleName
nested_items.description: The unique ID of the created vehicle.

nested_items.name: arn
nested_items.description: The ARN of the created vehicle.

nested_items.name: thingArn
nested_items.description: The ARN of a created or validated Amazon Web Services IoT thing.
